New Records: Travis Head's 154 not out is the highest score by an Australian in a one-day match played in England
Key Match Events: Travis Head smashes 20 fours and five sixes off 129 balls
Labuschagne took 3 for 39, as well as four catches, before his half-century
Head went on to grab the last two wickets in successive deliveries
Pre-Game Insights: Mitch Marsh's world champions had to rely on part-time spinners to help world-class tweaker Adam Zampa bowl out the hosts
The visiting slow bowlers contributed 30.4 of the 49.4 overs
Post-Match Reflections: Mitch Marsh said 'I'm very happy, that was a great win, especially after the start England got, and the way we were able to pull it back'
Travis Head smiled 'I've worked extremely hard over a few years and probably play the game a little bit more relaxed now, and take it for what it is'
Miscellaneous Highlights: England batted first after stand-in captain Harry Brook won the toss
Ben Duckett lashed 95 and Will Jacks 62 on a Trent Bridge belter
Australia took the last eight wickets for 102 as Marsh squeezed the best out of his happy band of occasional spinners
Others: Travis Head and Marnus Labuschagne formed an unbroken match-winning partnership of 148
Adam Zampa took three wickets to halt England's progress in the middle of the innings
Ben Dwarshuis picked up an apparent shoulder injury after bowling four overs
